summary: The thing about Peter Parker and arrogance is... weird. He thinks highly of himself and his abilities (at least of his...
body:
The thing about Peter Parker and arrogance is… weird.

He thinks highly of himself and his abilities (at least of his abilities, atm I don’t really remember him talking about his personality traits enough to explore that), but… it’s never inaccurate. Like, he’ll go “I’m a whiz kid, I’m so strong, I’m so fast, I’m so great” and then he puts his money where his mouth’s at.

But sometimes he’ll think those things and get his ass kicked (at least momentarily) by someone he thought he could easily defeat. Was it because he overestimated himself? No, it’s that he often underestimates his oponents the first time they fight. I haven’t read enough of other comics to know if this is just a constant strategy to show how powerful the villains are by surprising the heroes, but this is something that happens often in Spider-Man comics (at least until the 80′s, which is where I’m at. It might not be the case further on.)
